#!/usr/bin/env perl
use v5.40;
use FindBin;
use lib "$FindBin::Bin/../lib";
use Typist::LSP;
Typist::LSP->run;

__END__

=head1 NAME

typist-lsp - Language Server Protocol server for Typist

=head1 SYNOPSIS

    typist-lsp

    # With logging
    TYPIST_LSP_LOG=debug typist-lsp

    # With message tracing
    TYPIST_LSP_TRACE=/tmp/trace.jsonl typist-lsp

=head1 DESCRIPTION

A standalone LSP server that provides type-aware editor features for Perl
files using the Typist type system. Communicates over stdin/stdout using
the JSON-RPC protocol with Content-Length framing.

Supported capabilities: hover, completion, diagnostics, document symbols,
go-to-definition, signature help, and inlay hints.

=head1 ENVIRONMENT

=over 4

=item C<TYPIST_LSP_LOG>

Log level: C<off>, C<error>, C<warn>, C<info> (default), C<debug>, C<trace>.
Logs are written to stderr.

=item C<TYPIST_LSP_TRACE>

Path to a JSONL file for recording all LSP messages with timestamps.

=item C<TYPIST_CHECK_QUIET>

Set to C<1> to suppress CHECK-phase diagnostics (recommended when using
this server, as it provides the same diagnostics).

=back

=head1 SEE ALSO

L<Typist>, L<Typist::LSP::Server>

=cut
